vars: {
  d2-config: {
    layout-engine: elk
    theme-id: 4
  }
}

title: |'md
# Reactor Pattern: Component Architecture
*Demultiplexer → Dispatcher → Handler Table → Concrete Handlers*
'| {near: top-center}

reactor_boundary: "reactor internals" {
  style: {
    fill: "#E8EAF6"
    stroke: "#5C6BC0"
    stroke-width: 2
    stroke-dash: 0
    border-radius: 8
    font-size: 13
    font-color: "#3949AB"
    bold: true
  }

  demux: "Event Demultiplexer" {
    style: {
      fill: "#7B1FA2"
      font-color: white
      border-radius: 6
      shadow: true
    }
    label: |'md
**Event Demultiplexer**
`epoll_wait(epfd, events, MAX_EVENTS, timeout_ms)`
- Blocks until ≥1 fd is ready
- Returns `nready` (0–1024) `epoll_event` structs
- Each struct: `{uint32_t events, epoll_data_t data}`
- Timeout from timer heap: `compute_epoll_timeout()`
- `EINTR` → retry; other error → fatal
'|
    width: 380
  }

  dispatcher: "Dispatcher" {
    style: {
      fill: "#1565C0"
      font-color: white
      border-radius: 6
      shadow: true
    }
    label: |'md
**Dispatcher**
`for (i = 0; i < nready; i++) { … }`
1. Extract `fd = events[i].data.fd`
2. Check `h->registered && !h->closing`
3. Translate epoll flags → `REACTOR_READ | WRITE | ERROR`
4. Call `h->callback(fd, rev, h->udata)`
5. Guard: `dispatching = 1` during loop
'|
    width: 380
  }

  handler_table: "Handler Registration Table" {
    style: {
      fill: "#E65100"
      font-color: white
      border-radius: 6
      shadow: true
    }
    label: |'md
**Handler Registration Table**
`fd_handler_t handlers[max_fds]`

| Field | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `registered` | int | 0=free, 1=active |
| `closing` | int | mark-and-skip guard |
| `fd` | int | for assertions |
| `events` | uint32_t | EPOLLIN\|OUT\|ET |
| `callback` | fn ptr | user I/O cb |
| `udata` | void* | opaque user data |

*sizeof(fd_handler_t) = 32 bytes (1 cache line)*
'|
    width: 440
  }

  demux -> dispatcher: "nready epoll_events\n(12 bytes each, stack array)" {
    style.stroke: "#5C6BC0"
    style.stroke-width: 2
    style.bold: true
  }
  dispatcher -> handler_table: "handlers[fd] lookup\n(O(1) array index)" {
    style.stroke: "#5C6BC0"
    style.stroke-width: 2
    style.bold: true
  }
}

user_boundary: "user code  (zero epoll symbols)" {
  style: {
    fill: "#E8F5E9"
    stroke: "#388E3C"
    stroke-width: 2
    stroke-dash: 4
    border-radius: 8
    font-size: 13
    font-color: "#2E7D32"
    bold: true
  }

  accept_handler: "accept_handler()" {
    style: {
      fill: "#1B5E20"
      font-color: white
      border-radius: 5
    }
    label: |'md
**accept_handler**
`reactor_io_cb` registered on `listen_fd`
- Drains accept queue until `EAGAIN`
- Calls `reactor_register(r, conn_fd, REACTOR_READ, …)`
- Sets idle + header timers via `reactor_set_timeout`
- Allocates `http_conn_t` via `calloc`
'|
    width: 330
  }

  echo_handler: "echo_handler()" {
    style: {
      fill: "#33691E"
      font-color: white
      border-radius: 5
    }
    label: |'md
**echo_handler**
`reactor_io_cb` registered per connection
- `REACTOR_ERROR` → `echo_conn_close(c)`
- `REACTOR_READ` → drain loop until `EAGAIN`
  → `write(fd, buf, n)`
- Resets idle timer on each `read()` > 0
'|
    width: 330
  }

  http_io_callback: "http_io_callback()" {
    style: {
      fill: "#558B2F"
      font-color: white
      border-radius: 5
    }
    label: |'md
**http_io_callback**
`reactor_io_cb` — HTTP/1.1 state machine dispatcher
- `REACTOR_ERROR` → `http_conn_close(conn)`
- `REACTOR_READ` → `http_handle_read(conn)`
  → `http_try_parse()` → `http_process_request()`
- `REACTOR_WRITE` → `http_handle_write(conn)`
  → `write_buf` drain → EPOLLOUT lifecycle
- Defers `free(conn)` via `reactor_defer`
'|
    width: 330
  }
}

kernel: "Linux Kernel" {
  style: {
    fill: "#212121"
    font-color: white
    border-radius: 6
    shadow: true
    bold: true
  }
  label: |'md
**Linux Kernel**
NIC interrupt → DMA → socket receive buffer
→ epoll readiness queue entry added
→ `epoll_wait()` wakes calling thread
*Event sources: TCP data, EOF, RST, send-buffer drain*
'|
  width: 360
}

pending_ops: "Deferred Modification Queue" {
  style: {
    fill: "#F57F17"
    font-color: white
    border-radius: 5
    shadow: false
  }
  label: |'md
**Pending Ops Queue** *(re-entrancy safety)*
`pending_mod_t pending_ops[256]`
During dispatch (`dispatching=1`):
`reactor_register` → enqueues `PENDING_ADD/MOD`
`reactor_deregister` → enqueues `PENDING_DEL`, sets `closing=1`
Phase 2 (after dispatch): applies all ops via `epoll_ctl`
Phase 2 clears handler slots for `PENDING_DEL`
'|
  width: 360
}

kernel -> reactor_boundary.demux: "Hardware interrupt\n→ socket buffer filled\n→ fd added to readiness queue" {
  style.stroke: "#880E4F"
  style.stroke-width: 2
  style.bold: true
  style.font-color: "#880E4F"
}

reactor_boundary.handler_table -> user_boundary.accept_handler: "callback(listen_fd, REACTOR_READ, NULL)" {
  style.stroke: "#388E3C"
  style.stroke-width: 2
  style.stroke-dash: 3
}

reactor_boundary.handler_table -> user_boundary.echo_handler: "callback(conn_fd, REACTOR_READ|WRITE|ERROR, echo_conn_t*)" {
  style.stroke: "#388E3C"
  style.stroke-width: 2
  style.stroke-dash: 3
}

reactor_boundary.handler_table -> user_boundary.http_io_callback: "callback(conn_fd, REACTOR_READ|WRITE|ERROR, http_conn_t*)" {
  style.stroke: "#388E3C"
  style.stroke-width: 2
  style.stroke-dash: 3
}

user_boundary.accept_handler -> reactor_boundary.handler_table: "reactor_register(r, fd, events, cb, udata)\n→ enqueues PENDING_ADD if dispatching==1" {
  style.stroke: "#E65100"
  style.stroke-width: 1
  style.stroke-dash: 5
  style.font-color: "#E65100"
}

user_boundary.http_io_callback -> pending_ops: "reactor_deregister(r, fd)\nsets closing=1, enqueues PENDING_DEL" {
  style.stroke: "#F57F17"
  style.stroke-width: 1
  style.stroke-dash: 5
  style.font-color: "#BF360C"
}

pending_ops -> reactor_boundary.handler_table: "Phase 2: epoll_ctl(ADD|MOD|DEL)\nclears handler slot on DEL" {
  style.stroke: "#F57F17"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}

boundary_note: |'md
**Boundary Invariant**
User code (green zone) contains **zero** `epoll_*` symbols.
All kernel interaction is mediated by the reactor (blue zone).
The orange deferred queue makes callbacks re-entrancy-safe.
'| {
  near: bottom-center
  style.font-size: 11
  style.font-color: "#37474F"
}